--------------------------Constructor--------------------------
Constructor is the block just like method which is invoked at the time of object creation. 
The name of costructor should be same as class name.
The constructor body should not have return statement.
The constructor should not be declered with any return type.
Whenever a constructor is invoked, The body of constructor get executed.
A constructor is developed to initialize object variables at the time of object creation...
Every java class should have a constructor, if we don't develop a constructor the compiler write a constructor as default constructor.
